<HR><P> 

<H2> Biographical sketch </H2>

Mihir received his BS (in Mathematics) from the <!WA13><a href=
"http://www.caltech.edu"> California Institute of Technology</a> in
1986, and his Ph.D (in Computer Science) from the <!WA14><a href=
"http://web.mit.edu"> Massachusetts Institute of Technology</a> in
1991. From 1991 to 1995 he was at the <!WA15><a
href="http://www.watson.ibm.com"> IBM T.J. Watson Research Center</a>,
Hawthorne, New York, working in network security and complexity
theory.  He joined the <!WA16><a
href="http://www-cse.ucsd.edu/CSE_Home_Page.html"> Computer Science
and Engineering Department</a> of the <!WA17><a href="http://www.ucsd.edu">
University of California at San Diego </a> in October 1995 as
Assistant Professor. <P>

